00:40:34.780 --> 00:40:42.980
people kept the right number of people and
didn't tend to overly CYA their emails unnecessarily.

00:40:42.980 --> 00:40:49.670
So it's not necessarily about the reply to
all but when you over cc people on the email,

00:40:49.670 --> 00:40:55.660
reply to all can sometimes become dangerous
as the Air Force example gives us. But I'm

00:40:55.660 --> 00:40:59.440
not against it at all. I use it all the time.
